HEADWORD: Schoolhouse
<hw>School"house`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A house
appropriated for the use of a school or schools, or for
instruction.</def><-- a building used for schooling, esp. one used as an
elementary school; usu. small, and usu. constructed specifically for
that purpose. -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

